				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
							<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Imperial, or the US customary/st=
andard system, is based on the </span><i><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">o=
ld</span></i><span style=3D"font-weight: 400"> British imperial system of o=
unces, pounds, cups, pints, quarts, and gallons. The metric system is a dec=
imal system based on the meter, liter, and gram.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">While the United States (along with Mya=
nmar and Liberia) use the imperial system, the rest of the world uses the m=
etric system. This is why when you are reading a recipe from another countr=
y, the ingredients may be listed in liters or grams.</span></p>
						</div>
				</div>
