<ul>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">United Stat=
es imperial teaspoon =3D 4.93 ml</span></li>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Metric teas=
poon =3D 5 ml</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400"><strong>Tablespoon</strong>:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">United Stat=
es imperial tablespoon =3D 14.79 ml</span></li>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Metric tabl=
espoon =3D 15 ml</span></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Since the imperial and metric units are=
 so close, you can use a one-for-one swap and it will not impact the recipe=
. The only exception to this rule is the Australian tablespoon, which is 20=
